<h2>About KopiJunkie</h2>

<p>My name's <strong>Kimmi Gan</strong>. Welcome to <strong>{{site.title}}</strong> - my online home.</p>

<p>I've always loved experimenting with web technologies. Still do.</p>

<p>I like to create cool and engaging web sites, apps and user interfaces using modern web technologies. Having completed a Computer Science conversion course, I meddle with back end development too now. I also enjoy doing some graphics razzle dazzle on the side. Though currently, I'm more interested in visualisations like timelines and 3D text using just HTML and CSS instead. These days I also build mobile web apps.</p>

<p>I made my first web site on Geocities back in the 90s using MS Notepad (HTML coding) and MS Paint (very basic graphics) complete with autoplaying MIDI sound file and a blinking, scrolling marquee. Basically everything a web site should be <strong>plus</strong> everything it shouldn't be. But don't worry, I'm wiser now having made other web sites as voluntary work or for fun over the years. Definitely way past that phase now and I know better than to develop something tacky.</p>

