<p>I'm a Malaysian girl geek currently based in London after completing a masters degree at the <a href="http://www.bristol.ac.uk/" target="_blank">University of Bristol</a>. I used to work in Singapore handling corporate events and conference services in a 5-star hotel before venturing back to university to learn about the science of computers. Before working life, I studied at <a href="http://www.monash.edu.au/" target="_blank">Monash University</a>, Australia majoring in Mass Communication. (Yes, I've been around quite a bit!)</p>

<p>I have a strong interest in digital media technology. Or rather how digital technology can be used to deliver media and information. Web development, specifically front end development, was the perfect fit for my interest in bringing mass media (what I studied previously) and technology (my current skill set) together.</p>

<p>Right now, I'm a Front End Developer at a tech startup, <a href="http://www.cube19.com" target="_blank">cube19</a>, working on a visual analytics web app product. Previously I was at a digital agency, <a href="http://www.vexeddigital.com/" target="_blank">Vexed Digital</a> (now known as <a href="http://www.futureplatforms.com/" target="_blank">Future Platforms</a>) making web sites and apps for a variety of clients including Domino's Pizza and De Vere Group.</p>

